  "text": "A cDNA encoding D2 was cloned from Rana catesbeiana tissues [CITATION_1] , and its mammalian counterpart was subsequently isolated from rat brown fat [CITATION_2] . In humans, D2 mRNA was unexpectedly detected in thyroid gland and other tissues, suggesting previously unrecognized roles of D2 in those tissues (10 -13) .",
